headline: KEYS Q3 Deep Dive: AI Momentum, Tariff Pressures, and Demand Diversification Shape Outlook
summary: Electronic measurement provider Keysight (NYSE:KEYS) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 11.1% year on year to $1.35 billion. Guidance for next quarter’s revenue was better than expected at $1.38 billion at the midpoint, 0.7% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.72 per share was 2.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
